 Over half a century after the Seine was declared biologically dead, Paris mayor Anne Hidalgo dipped into the river yesterday and declared it sufficiently clean for Olympic swimming competitions.\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 256, \"end\": 261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999997710347, \"rank\": 1.1724388835112377e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 294, \"end\": 299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 2.471804829713803e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 306, \"end\": 318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Getty\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 224}, {\"ngram\": \"half a century\", \"from\": 230, \"to\": 244}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 339}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic swimming competitions\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 418}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Under the gaze of a contingent of soldiers and police officers, and surrounded by an entourage of swimsuit-wearing city employees, Ms Hidalgo's symbolic swim in the turquoise-brownish waters was broadcast live on national television.\", \"from\": 422, \"to\": 655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 556, \"end\": 563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999999997205578, \"rank\": 2.7936057507122814e-10, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the gaze\", \"from\": 428, \"to\": 436}, {\"ngram\": \"a contingent\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 452}, {\"ngram\": \"soldiers\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 464}, {\"ngram\": \"police officers\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 484}, {\"ngram\": \"an entourage\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 516}, {\"ngram\": \"swimsuit-wearing city employees\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 551}, {\"ngram\": \"the turquoise-brownish waters\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"national television\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hundreds of spectators also watched from the riverbanks and nearby bridges.\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 731, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hundreds\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 664}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 678}, {\"ngram\": \"the riverbanks\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 711}, {\"ngram\": \"nearby bridges\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's pure happiness,\\\" Ms Hidalgo said after she climbed out, having fulfilled her pledge to swim in the Seine before the Olympic Games start in nine days.\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 759, \"end\": 766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999999997205578, \"rank\": 2.7936057507122814e-10, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}, {\"begin\": 838, \"end\": 843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999997710347, \"rank\": 1.1724388835112377e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"pure happiness\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 753}, {\"ngram\": \"her pledge\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 822}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 868}, {\"ngram\": \"nine days\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 887}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yesterday's dip marked what French officials hope to be the end of a years-long nail-biter.\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 918, \"end\": 924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.725883041954905, \"rank\": 0.19662731602710412, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Yesterday's dip\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 905}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 953}, {\"ngram\": \"a years-long nail-biter\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 980}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming in the Seine has been banned for a century because of health concerns, primarily due to wastewater that sometimes overflows from the city's old sewerage system into the Seine.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 998, \"end\": 1003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999997710347, \"rank\": 1.1724388835112377e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1160, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999997710347, \"rank\": 1.1724388835112377e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a century\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1033}, {\"ngram\": \"health concerns\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"wastewater\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1089}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's old sewerage system\", \"from\": 1120, \"to\": 1150}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2015, Ms Hidalgo surprisingly announced a bold plan to make the river the star of the Olympic Games, with plans for a floating Opening Ceremonies and swimming competitions in the river.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1179, \"end\": 1186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999999997205578, \"rank\": 2.7936057507122814e-10, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bold plan\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1221}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1239}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1269}, {\"ngram\": \"plans\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1281}, {\"ngram\": \"a floating Opening Ceremonies\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming competitions\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1341}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1354}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But despite \\u20ac1.37bn of investment, bacteria levels long remained above safe limits, leading to the cancellation of the swimming portion of Paralympic triathlon tests and of the Open Water Swimming World Cup last summer.\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1576, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"investment\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1390}, {\"ngram\": \"bacteria levels\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"safe limits\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1439}, {\"ngram\": \"the cancellation\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1468}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming portion\", \"from\": 1472, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"Paralympic triathlon tests\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1522}, {\"ngram\": \"the Open Water Swimming World Cup\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1563}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year, the Surfrider Foundation environmental group reported \\\"alarming\\\" contamination, with testing at one site over six months showing higher-than-recommended levels of E coli and enterococci bacteria.\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1784, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1593, \"end\": 1613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfrider_Foundation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Surfrider Foundation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfrider_Foundation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfrider_Foundation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\\"alarming\\\" contamination\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1667}, {\"ngram\": \"one site\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"six months\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1709}, {\"ngram\": \"higher-than-recommended levels\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1748}, {\"ngram\": \"E coli\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1758}, {\"ngram\": \"enterococci bacteria\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1783}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris mayor's promised swim had to be repeatedly postponed, with explanations ranging from excessive rainfall to - most recently - France's political turmoil.\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1789, \"end\": 1794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 2.471804829713803e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1920, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7065623024800446, \"rank\": 0.3434513807461259, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"explanations\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1866}, {\"ngram\": \"excessive rainfall\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1898}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As recently as last month, the ambitious project threatened to become an embarrassment.\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 2036, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"last month\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"the ambitious project\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1997}, {\"ngram\": \"an embarrassment\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials were for the first time talking about a plan B for the highly anticipated Seine competitions.\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2140, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2121, \"end\": 2126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999997710347, \"rank\": 1.1724388835112377e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Officials\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2046}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2070}, {\"ngram\": \"a plan B\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the gloom has given way to new enthusiasm in recent days, as the weather improved and the Seine's water quality reached safe limits on most days this month, according to city measurements.\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2236, \"end\": 2241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999997710347, \"rank\": 1.1724388835112377e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the gloom\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2155}, {\"ngram\": \"way\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2169}, {\"ngram\": \"new enthusiasm\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2187}, {\"ngram\": \"recent days\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2202}, {\"ngram\": \"the weather\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2218}, {\"ngram\": \"safe limits\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"most days\", \"from\": 2281, 